ew StatefulSet, and then use index-level shard allocation filtering to move shards to those warm nodes. The verification only requires some shards to be on the new nodes, not all of them, so I need to apply the right allocation constraints. index allocation policy on the app-data index to force the shards onto the warm tier nodes. I'm thinking through the discovery configuration for the new nodes—they'll need to reference the existing master nodes' DNS entries to join the cluster, and since the cluster is already formed, I don't need to worry about the initial bootstrap settings.\n\nThe new data pods will be able to resolve the headless service DNS names since they're in the same namespace, so discovery should work fine. I should also provision PVCs for the new pods to match the existing StatefulSet's storage setup.\n\nWriting the ConfigMap manifest... Configuring the data node StatefulSet with two replicas, setting up the Elasticsearch container with memory limits and health checks... Writing volume claims and tier routing...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":602,"cache_read_input_tokens":32032,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":602},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3c889f5e-8ca1-4715-8f0d-40ff900d6340","uuid":"9ba32b71-4335-4316-a4f2-74d31e4837b0","request_id":"req_011CcREqgkL5juAdXmdgWZUk"}
